{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1031,"text":"(Music: \"The Sound of Silence,\"\nSimon &amp; Garfunkel)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":3539,"text":"Hello voice mail, my old friend."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":7687,"text":"I've called for tech support again."},{"time":11568,"text":"I ignored my boss's warning."},{"time":15197,"text":"I called on a Monday morning."},{"time":18537,"text":"Now it's evening, and my dinner\nfirst grew cold, and then grew mold."},{"time":24679,"text":"I'm still on hold."},{"time":26977,"text":"I'm listening to the sounds of silence."},{"time":32585,"text":"I don't think you understand."},{"time":35666,"text":"I think your phone lines are unmanned."},{"time":39516,"text":"I punched every touch tone I was told,"},{"time":42812,"text":"but I've still spent 18 hours on hold."},{"time":45999,"text":"It's not enough your software\ncrashed my Mac,"},{"time":49000,"text":"and it constantly hangs and bombs --"},{"time":52561,"text":"it erased my ROMs!"},{"time":55145,"text":"Now the Mac makes the sounds of silence."},{"time":60309,"text":"In my dreams I fantasize"},{"time":63666,"text":"of wreaking vengeance on you guys."},{"time":67265,"text":"Say your motorcycle crashes."},{"time":70764,"text":"Blood comes gushing from your gashes."},{"time":74095,"text":"With your fading strength, you call 9-1-1\nand you pray for a trained MD."},{"time":80702,"text":"But you get me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82346,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":83813,"text":"And you listen to the sounds of silence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88035,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90948,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":93170,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94345,"text":"Good evening and welcome to:"},{"time":95717,"text":"\"Spot the TED Presenter Who Used\nto Be a Broadway Accompanist.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":98729,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":99891,"text":"When I was offered the Times\ncolumn six years ago,"},{"time":103430,"text":"the deal was like this:"},{"time":104662,"text":"you'll be sent the coolest, hottest,\nslickest new gadgets."},{"time":108065,"text":"Every week, it'll arrive at your door."},{"time":110000,"text":"You get to try them out,\nplay with them, evaluate them"},{"time":112677,"text":"until the novelty wears out,\nbefore you have to send them back,"},{"time":115773,"text":"and you'll get paid for it."},{"time":117124,"text":"You can think about it, if you want."},{"time":119646,"text":"So, I've always been a technology nut,\nand I absolutely love it."},{"time":124295,"text":"The job, though, came with one\nsmall downside, and that is,"},{"time":127256,"text":"they intended to publish my email address\nat the end of every column."},{"time":132840,"text":"And what I've noticed is -- first of all,\nyou get an incredible amount of email."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138079,"text":"If you ever are feeling lonely,"},{"time":139838,"text":"get a New York Times column,"},{"time":141242,"text":"because you will get hundreds\nand hundreds and hundreds of emails."},{"time":144400,"text":"And the email I'm getting a lot\ntoday is about frustration."},{"time":148000,"text":"People are feeling like things --"},{"time":151373,"text":"Ok, I just had an alarm\ncome up on my screen."},{"time":153707,"text":"Lucky you can't see it."},{"time":155120,"text":"People are feeling overwhelmed."},{"time":156643,"text":"They're feeling like\nit's too much technology, too fast."},{"time":159287,"text":"It may be good technology,"},{"time":161000,"text":"but I feel like there's not enough\nof a support structure."},{"time":164012,"text":"There's not enough help."},{"time":165618,"text":"There's not enough thought\nput into the design of it"},{"time":168088,"text":"to make it easy and enjoyable to use."},{"time":170042,"text":"One time I wrote a column about my efforts\nto reach Dell Technical Support,"},{"time":174054,"text":"and within 12 hours,\nthere were 700 messages"},{"time":178167,"text":"from readers on the feedback boards\non the Times website,"},{"time":181382,"text":"from users saying,"},{"time":183298,"text":"\"\"Me too, and here's my tale of woe.\""},{"time":185736,"text":"I call it \"software rage.\""},{"time":188146,"text":"And man, let me tell you,"},{"time":189369,"text":"whoever figures out how to make money\noff of this frustration will --"},{"time":193816,"text":"Oh, how did that\nget up there? Just kidding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196121,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":197293,"text":"Ok, so why is the problem accelerating?"},{"time":200196,"text":"And part of the problem is, ironically,"},{"time":202185,"text":"because the industry\nhas put so much thought"},{"time":204304,"text":"into making things easier to use."},{"time":206281,"text":"I'll show you what I mean."},{"time":207906,"text":"This is what the computer\ninterface used to look like, DOS."},{"time":212365,"text":"Over the years, it's gotten easier to use."},{"time":215223,"text":"This is the original Mac operating system."},{"time":217803,"text":"Reagan was President.\nMadonna was still a brunette."},{"time":220938,"text":"And the entire operating system --"},{"time":222691,"text":"this is the good part -- the entire\noperating system fit in 211 k."},{"time":227875,"text":"You couldn't put\nthe Mac OS X logo in 211 k!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":231001,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":232637,"text":"So the irony is, that as these\nthings became easier to use,"},{"time":236464,"text":"a less technical, broader audience\nwas coming into contact"},{"time":240344,"text":"with this equipment for the first time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242313,"text":"I once had the distinct privilege\nof sitting in on the Apple call center"},{"time":248002,"text":"for a day."},{"time":249186,"text":"The guy had a duplicate headset\nfor me to listen to."},{"time":252000,"text":"And the calls that --\nyou know how they say,"},{"time":255550,"text":"\"Your call may be recorded\nfor quality assurance?\""},{"time":258304,"text":"Uh-uh."},{"time":259597,"text":"Your call may be recorded"},{"time":261000,"text":"so that they can collect\nthe funniest dumb user stories"},{"time":263692,"text":"and pass them around on a CD."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265207,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266271,"text":"Which they do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":269616,"text":"And I have a copy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270862,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":271909,"text":"It's in your gift bag. No, no."},{"time":274027,"text":"With your voices on it!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":276222,"text":"So, some of the stories are just\nso classic, and yet so understandable."},{"time":281405,"text":"A woman called Apple to complain\nthat her mouse was squeaking."},{"time":284772,"text":"Making a squeaking noise."},{"time":286018,"text":"And the technician said,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287212,"text":"\"Well, ma'am, what do you mean\nyour mouse is squeaking?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":289887,"text":"She says, \"All I can tell you\nis that it squeaks louder,"},{"time":292554,"text":"the faster I move it across the screen.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":295188,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":297283,"text":"And the technician's like,"},{"time":298569,"text":"\"Ma'am, you've got the mouse\nup against the screen?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":301743,"text":"She goes, \"Well, the message said,\n'Click here to continue.'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":304860,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":307949,"text":"Well, if you like that one --\nhow much time have we got?"},{"time":311822,"text":"Another one, a guy called --\nthis is absolutely true --"},{"time":314518,"text":"his computer had crashed,\nand he told the technician"},{"time":317000,"text":"he couldn't restart it, no matter\nhow many times he typed \"11.\""},{"time":321218,"text":"And the technician said,\n\"What? Why are you typing 11?\""},{"time":324392,"text":"He said, \"The message says,\n'Error Type 11.'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":328000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":332399,"text":"So, we must admit"},{"time":335328,"text":"that some of the blame falls squarely\nat the feet of the users."},{"time":340573,"text":"But why is the technical overload crisis,"},{"time":343000,"text":"the complexity crisis, accelerating now?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345604,"text":"In the hardware world, it's because\nwe the consumers want"},{"time":348407,"text":"everything to be smaller,\nsmaller, smaller."},{"time":350615,"text":"So the gadgets are getting\ntinier and tinier,"},{"time":353202,"text":"but our fingers are essentially\nstaying the same size."},{"time":355829,"text":"So it gets to be more and more\nof a challenge."},{"time":358000,"text":"Software is subject\nto another primal force:"},{"time":360120,"text":"the mandate to release\nmore and more versions."},{"time":362733,"text":"When you buy a piece of software,"},{"time":364353,"text":"it's not like buying a vase\nor a candy bar, where you own it."},{"time":367265,"text":"It's more like joining a club,\nwhere you pay dues every year,"},{"time":370657,"text":"and every year, they say,"},{"time":371936,"text":"\"We've added more features,\nand we'll sell it to you for $99.\""},{"time":376000,"text":"I know one guy who's spent $4,000\njust on Photoshop over the years."},{"time":381000,"text":"And software companies make\n35 percent of their revenue"},{"time":383863,"text":"from just these software upgrades."},{"time":385643,"text":"I call it the Software Upgrade Paradox --"},{"time":388542,"text":"which is that if you improve\na piece of software enough times,"},{"time":392415,"text":"you eventually ruin it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393934,"text":"I mean, Microsoft Word was last\njust a word processor in, you know,"},{"time":398123,"text":"the Eisenhower administration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399713,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":400785,"text":"But what's the alternative?"},{"time":402172,"text":"Microsoft actually did this experiment."},{"time":404208,"text":"They said, \"Well, wait a minute."},{"time":405780,"text":"Everyone complains that\nwe're adding so many features."},{"time":408352,"text":"Let's create a word processor\nthat's just a word processor:"},{"time":411175,"text":"Simple, pure; does not do web pages,\nis not a database.\""},{"time":414428,"text":"And it came out,\nand it was called Microsoft Write."},{"time":417858,"text":"And none of you are nodding\nin acknowledgment, because it died."},{"time":421000,"text":"It tanked. No one ever bought it."},{"time":423000,"text":"I call this the Sport Utility Principle."},{"time":425427,"text":"People like to surround themselves\nwith unnecessary power, right?"},{"time":429691,"text":"They don't need the database\nand the website, but they're like,"},{"time":433024,"text":"\"Well, I'll upgrade, because, I might,\nyou know, I might need that someday.\""},{"time":437000,"text":"So the problem is: as you add more\nfeatures, where are they going to go?"},{"time":440582,"text":"Where are you going to stick them?\nYou only have so many design tools."},{"time":444746,"text":"You can do buttons, you can do\nsliders, pop-up menus, sub-menus."},{"time":448762,"text":"But if you're not careful\nabout how you choose,"},{"time":451811,"text":"you wind up with this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":454771,"text":"This is an un-retouched --\nthis is not a joke --"},{"time":457627,"text":"un-retouched photo of Microsoft Word,"},{"time":459913,"text":"the copy that you have,\nwith all the toolbars open."},{"time":462771,"text":"You've obviously never\nopened all the toolbars,"},{"time":466117,"text":"but all you have to type in\nis this little, teeny window down here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470883,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":473466,"text":"And we've arrived at the age\nof interface matrices,"},{"time":476935,"text":"where there are so many\nfeatures and options,"},{"time":479101,"text":"you have to do two dimensions, you know:"},{"time":481045,"text":"a vertical and a horizontal."},{"time":482412,"text":"You guys all complain"},{"time":483593,"text":"about how Microsoft Word\nis always bulleting your lists"},{"time":486355,"text":"and underlining your links automatically."},{"time":488473,"text":"The off switch is in there somewhere."},{"time":491632,"text":"I'm telling you -- it's there."},{"time":493235,"text":"Part of the art of designing\na simple, good interface,"},{"time":496503,"text":"is knowing when to use\nwhich one of these features."},{"time":500011,"text":"So, here is the log-off\ndialogue box for Windows 2000."},{"time":503560,"text":"There are only four choices,"},{"time":506084,"text":"so why are they in a pop-up menu?"},{"time":509164,"text":"It's not like the rest of the screen\nis so full of other components"},{"time":512504,"text":"that you need to collapse the choices."},{"time":515000,"text":"They could have put them all out in view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517000,"text":"Here's Apple's take\non the exact same dialogue box."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":521427,"text":"Thank you -- yes, I designed\nthe dialogue box. No, no."},{"time":525000,"text":"Already, we can see\nthat Apple and Microsoft"},{"time":527639,"text":"have a severely divergent\napproach to software design."},{"time":531799,"text":"Microsoft's approach\nto simplicity tends to be:"},{"time":535156,"text":"let's break it down;\nlet's just make it more steps."},{"time":538000,"text":"There are these \"wizards\" everywhere."},{"time":540000,"text":"And you know, there's a new version\nof Windows coming out this fall."},{"time":543263,"text":"If they continue at this pace,\nthere's absolutely no telling"},{"time":546342,"text":"where they might wind up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548512,"text":"[Welcome to the Type a Word Wizard]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":550874,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":552066,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":555380,"text":"\"Welcome to the Type a Word Wizard.\""},{"time":557189,"text":"Ok, I'll bite."},{"time":558428,"text":"Let's click \"Next\" to continue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":563327,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":565198,"text":"From the drop-down menu, choose\nthe first letter you want to type. Ok."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568572,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570929,"text":"So there is a limit\nthat we don't want to cross."},{"time":573492,"text":"So what is the answer?"},{"time":574667,"text":"How do you pack in all these features\nin a simple, intelligent way?"},{"time":578767,"text":"I believe in consistency, when possible,"},{"time":581496,"text":"real-world equivalents,"},{"time":582822,"text":"trash can folder, when possible,\nlabel things, mostly."},{"time":586069,"text":"But I beg of the designers here"},{"time":588269,"text":"to break all those rules\nif they violate the biggest rule of all,"},{"time":591864,"text":"which is intelligence."},{"time":593077,"text":"Now what do I mean by that?"},{"time":594404,"text":"I'm going to give you some examples"},{"time":596119,"text":"where intelligence makes something\nnot consistent, but it's better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599475,"text":"If you are buying something on the web,"},{"time":601886,"text":"you're supposed to put in your address,"},{"time":603791,"text":"and you're supposed to choose\nwhat country you're from, ok?"},{"time":606649,"text":"There are 200 countries in the world."},{"time":608451,"text":"We like to think of the Internet\nas a global village."},{"time":610983,"text":"I'm sorry; it's not one yet."},{"time":612378,"text":"It's mainly like, the United States,\nEurope, and Japan."},{"time":615006,"text":"So why is \"United States\" in the \"U\"s?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":617381,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":618771,"text":"You have to scroll, like,\nseven screensful to get to it."},{"time":621724,"text":"Now, it would be inconsistent\nto put \"United States\" first,"},{"time":625000,"text":"but it would be intelligent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626495,"text":"This one's been touched on before,"},{"time":629152,"text":"but why in God's name do you\nshut down a Windows PC"},{"time":633000,"text":"by clicking a button called \"Start?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":635423,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":639515,"text":"Here's another pet one of mine:\nyou have a printer."},{"time":643000,"text":"Most of the time, you want to print\none copy of your document,"},{"time":646893,"text":"in page order, on that printer."},{"time":649169,"text":"So why in God's name do you see\nthis every time you print?"},{"time":653794,"text":"It's like a 747 shuttle cockpit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656286,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":657873,"text":"And one of the buttons at the bottom,\nyou'll notice, is not \"Print.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":661665,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":669294,"text":"Now, I'm not saying that Apple\nis the only company who has embraced"},{"time":673247,"text":"the cult of simplicity."},{"time":675827,"text":"Palm is also, especially in the old days,\nwonderful about this."},{"time":678831,"text":"I actually got to speak to Palm\nwhen they were flying high in the '90s,"},{"time":682213,"text":"and after the talk,\nI met one of the employees."},{"time":684441,"text":"He says, \"Nice talk.\" And I said,\n\"Thank you. What do you do here?\""},{"time":687646,"text":"He said, \"I'm a tap counter.\"\nI'm like, \"You're a what?\""},{"time":690311,"text":"He goes, \"Well Jeff Hawkins,\nthe CEO, says,"},{"time":692367,"text":"'If any task on the Palm Pilot\ntakes more than three taps of the stylus,"},{"time":696600,"text":"it's too long,\nand it has to be redesigned.'"},{"time":699622,"text":"So I'm the tap counter.\""},{"time":701414,"text":"So, I'm going to show you an example"},{"time":703200,"text":"of a company that does not\nhave a tap counter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705846,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":707133,"text":"This is Microsoft Word."},{"time":708728,"text":"Ok, when you want to create\na new blank document in Word --"},{"time":712886,"text":"it could happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714062,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":719434,"text":"You go up to the \"File\" menu\nand you choose \"New.\""},{"time":722917,"text":"Now, what happens when you choose \"New?\""},{"time":725140,"text":"Do you get a new blank document?"},{"time":727193,"text":"You do not."},{"time":728408,"text":"On the opposite side of the monitor,\na task bar appears,"},{"time":733123,"text":"and somewhere in those links --\nby the way, not at the top --"},{"time":736909,"text":"somewhere in those links is a button\nthat makes you a new document."},{"time":741377,"text":"Ok, so that is a company\nnot counting taps."},{"time":744394,"text":"You know, I don't want to just stand\nhere and make fun of Microsoft ..."},{"time":748222,"text":"Yes, I do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749548,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":751000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":754619,"text":"The Bill Gates song!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":756017,"text":"(Piano music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":757469,"text":"I've been a geek forever"},{"time":760928,"text":"and I wrote the very first DOS."},{"time":765168,"text":"I put my software and IBM together;"},{"time":768727,"text":"I got profit and they got the loss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":774702,"text":"I write the code\nthat makes the whole world run."},{"time":779344,"text":"I'm getting royalties from everyone."},{"time":783781,"text":"Sometimes it's garbage,\nbut the press is snowed."},{"time":788431,"text":"You buy the box; I'll sell the code."},{"time":794113,"text":"Every software company\nis doing Microsoft's R&amp;D."},{"time":799000,"text":"You can't keep a good idea\ndown these days."},{"time":803156,"text":"Even Windows is a hack."},{"time":805359,"text":"We're kind of based loosely on the Mac."},{"time":807709,"text":"So it's big, so it's slow.\nYou've got nowhere to go."},{"time":810441,"text":"I'm not doing this for praise."},{"time":813642,"text":"I write the code\nthat fits the world today."},{"time":818483,"text":"Big mediocrity in every way."},{"time":822704,"text":"We've entered planet domination mode."},{"time":827000,"text":"You'll have no choice; you'll buy my code."},{"time":832902,"text":"I am Bill Gates and I write the code."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840173,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":848000,"text":"But actually, I believe\nthere are really two Microsofts."},{"time":850726,"text":"There's the old one, responsible\nfor Windows and Office."},{"time":853829,"text":"They're dying to throw the whole thing\nout and start fresh, but they can't."},{"time":857867,"text":"They're locked in, because so many add-ons\nand other company stuff"},{"time":861591,"text":"locks into the old 1982 chassis."},{"time":864236,"text":"But there's also a new Microsoft,"},{"time":865850,"text":"that's really doing good,\nsimple interface designs."},{"time":869365,"text":"I liked the Media Center PC."},{"time":870945,"text":"I liked the Microsoft SPOT Watch."},{"time":872725,"text":"The Wireless Watch\nflopped miserably in the market,"},{"time":875702,"text":"but it wasn't because it wasn't\nsimply and beautifully designed."},{"time":878774,"text":"But let's put it this way:"},{"time":880044,"text":"would you pay $10 a month to have a watch"},{"time":882559,"text":"that has to be recharged\nevery night like your cell phone,"},{"time":885841,"text":"and stops working\nwhen you leave your area code?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":888404,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":891026,"text":"So, the signs might indicate"},{"time":893551,"text":"that the complexity crunch\nis only going to get worse."},{"time":896412,"text":"So is there any hope?"},{"time":898089,"text":"The screens are getting smaller,\npeople are illuminating,"},{"time":900812,"text":"putting manuals in the boxes,"},{"time":902233,"text":"things are coming out at a faster pace."},{"time":905000,"text":"It's funny -- when Steve Jobs\ncame back to Apple in 1997,"},{"time":908417,"text":"after 12 years away,\nit was the MacWorld Expo --"},{"time":911266,"text":"he came to the stage\nin that black turtleneck and jeans,"},{"time":914432,"text":"and he sort of did this."},{"time":915608,"text":"The crowd went wild,\nbut I had just seen --"},{"time":918000,"text":"I'm like, where have I seen this before?"},{"time":919950,"text":"I had just seen the movie \"Evita\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":921783,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":924892,"text":"with Madonna,"},{"time":926074,"text":"and I'm like, you know what?"},{"time":927846,"text":"I've got to do one about Steve Jobs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930967,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":931999,"text":"It won't be easy.\nYou'll think I'm strange."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935039,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":936207,"text":"When I try to explain why I'm back,"},{"time":938540,"text":"after telling the press\nApple's future is black."},{"time":941655,"text":"You won't believe me."},{"time":944274,"text":"All that you see is a kid in his teens\nwho started out in a garage"},{"time":949000,"text":"with only a buddy named Woz."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":953576,"text":"You try rhyming with garage!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":955333,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":957799,"text":"Don't cry for me, Cupertino."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960698,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":962044,"text":"The truth is, I never left you."},{"time":965000,"text":"I know the ropes now,\nknow what the tricks are."},{"time":968559,"text":"I made a fortune over at Pixar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":973063,"text":"Don't cry for me, Cupertino."},{"time":976182,"text":"I've still got the drive and vision."},{"time":979519,"text":"I still wear sandals in any weather."},{"time":982995,"text":"It's just that these days,"},{"time":985000,"text":"they're Gucci leather."}]},{"cues":[{"time":987000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":989000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":996258,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":997815,"text":"So Steve Jobs had always believed\nin simplicity and elegance and beauty."},{"time":1002547,"text":"And the truth is,"},{"time":1004468,"text":"for years I was a little depressed,"},{"time":1006620,"text":"because Americans\nobviously did not value it,"},{"time":1008917,"text":"because the Mac had\nthree percent market share,"},{"time":1011218,"text":"Windows had 95 percent market share --"},{"time":1013099,"text":"people did not think it was worth\nputting a price on it."},{"time":1016000,"text":"So I was a little depressed."},{"time":1017815,"text":"And then I heard Al Gore's talk,"},{"time":1019396,"text":"and I realized I didn't know\nthe meaning of depressed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021959,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023000,"text":"But it turns out I was wrong, right?"},{"time":1024761,"text":"Because the iPod came out,"},{"time":1026518,"text":"and it violated every bit\nof common wisdom."},{"time":1029160,"text":"Other products cost less;\nother products had more features,"},{"time":1032160,"text":"they had voice recorders\nand FM transmitters."},{"time":1034921,"text":"The other products were backed\nby Microsoft, with an open standard,"},{"time":1038167,"text":"not Apple's propriety standard."},{"time":1039905,"text":"But the iPod won --\nthis is the one they wanted."},{"time":1042501,"text":"The lesson was: simplicity sells."},{"time":1044788,"text":"And there are signs that the industry\nis getting the message."},{"time":1047686,"text":"This is a little company that's done\nvery well with simplicity and elegance."},{"time":1051301,"text":"The Sonos thing -- it's catching on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053064,"text":"I've got just a couple examples."},{"time":1054786,"text":"Physically, a really cool,\nelegant thinking coming along lately."},{"time":1058486,"text":"When you have a digital camera,"},{"time":1060463,"text":"how do you get the pictures\nback to your computer?"},{"time":1063730,"text":"Well, you either haul around a USB cable,"},{"time":1066096,"text":"or you buy a card reader\nand haul that around."},{"time":1068276,"text":"Either one, you're going to lose."},{"time":1069887,"text":"What I do is, I take out the memory card,"},{"time":1072370,"text":"and I fold it in half,\nrevealing USB contacts."},{"time":1077739,"text":"I just stick it in the computer,\noffload the pictures,"},{"time":1080421,"text":"put it right back in the camera."},{"time":1081984,"text":"I never have to lose anything."},{"time":1083808,"text":"Here's another example."},{"time":1085369,"text":"Chris, you're the source of all power.\nWill you be my power plug?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1088463,"text":"Chris Anderson: Oh yeah.\nDP: Hold that and don't let go."},{"time":1091227,"text":"You might've seen this,\nthis is Apple's new laptop."},{"time":1093672,"text":"This the power cord.\nIt hooks on like this."},{"time":1095720,"text":"And I'm sure every one of you has done\nthis at some point in your lives,"},{"time":1099141,"text":"or one of your children."},{"time":1100340,"text":"You walk along -- and I'm\nabout to pull this onto the floor."},{"time":1103189,"text":"I don't care. It's a loaner."},{"time":1104549,"text":"Here we go. Whoa!"},{"time":1105756,"text":"It's magnetic -- it doesn't pull\nthe laptop onto the floor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1108849,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1113000,"text":"In my very last example --"},{"time":1114993,"text":"I do a lot of my work\nusing speech recognition software."},{"time":1118993,"text":"And I'll just --\nyou have to be kind of quiet"},{"time":1121247,"text":"because the software is nervous."},{"time":1123524,"text":"Speech recognition\nsoftware is really great"},{"time":1125628,"text":"for doing emails very quickly; period."},{"time":1128182,"text":"Like, I get hundreds of them\na day; period."},{"time":1130845,"text":"And it's not just what I dictate\nthat it writes down; period."},{"time":1134160,"text":"I also use this feature\ncalled voice macros; period."},{"time":1138920,"text":"Correct \"dissuade.\""},{"time":1143999,"text":"Not \"just.\""},{"time":1147248,"text":"Ok, this is not an ideal situation,"},{"time":1148954,"text":"because it's getting the echo\nfrom the hall and stuff."},{"time":1151517,"text":"The point is, I can respond to people\nvery quickly by saying a short word,"},{"time":1155777,"text":"and having it write out\na much longer thing."},{"time":1157873,"text":"So if somebody\nsends me a fan letter, I'll say,"},{"time":1160263,"text":"\"Thanks for that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1161444,"text":"[Thank you so much\nfor taking the time to write ...]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1163975,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1165000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1168000,"text":"And conversely, if somebody\nsends me hate mail --"},{"time":1172462,"text":"which happens daily --"},{"time":1174788,"text":"I say, \"Piss off.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1179508,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1180849,"text":"[I admire your frankness ...]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1183345,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1185000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1190377,"text":"So that's my dirty little secret.\nDon't tell anyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1193000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1194139,"text":"So the point is --\nthis is a really interesting story."},{"time":1197000,"text":"This is version eight of this software,"},{"time":1198902,"text":"and do you know what they put\nin version eight?"},{"time":1201124,"text":"No new features. It's never\nhappened before in software!"},{"time":1204210,"text":"The company put no new features."},{"time":1205965,"text":"They just said, \"We'll make\nthis software work right.\" Right?"},{"time":1209604,"text":"Because for years, people had bought\nthis software, tried it out --"},{"time":1212844,"text":"95 percent accuracy was all they got,"},{"time":1214669,"text":"which means one in 20 words is wrong --"},{"time":1216589,"text":"and they'd put it in their drawer."},{"time":1218240,"text":"And the company got sick of that,"},{"time":1219844,"text":"so they said, \"This version,\nwe're not going to do anything,"},{"time":1222704,"text":"but make sure it's darned accurate.\""},{"time":1224461,"text":"And so that's what they did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1225834,"text":"This cult of doing things right\nis starting to spread."},{"time":1228446,"text":"So, my final advice for those of you\nwho are consumers of this technology:"},{"time":1231966,"text":"remember, if it doesn't work,\nit's not necessarily you, ok?"},{"time":1236000,"text":"It could be the design\nof the thing you're using."},{"time":1238358,"text":"Be aware in life\nof good design and bad design."},{"time":1241170,"text":"And if you're among the people\nwho create this stuff:"},{"time":1244061,"text":"Easy is hard."},{"time":1245404,"text":"Pre-sweat the details for your audience."},{"time":1247762,"text":"Count the taps."},{"time":1249000,"text":"Remember, the hard part\nis not deciding what features to add,"},{"time":1251967,"text":"it's deciding what to leave out."},{"time":1253760,"text":"And best of all, your motivation is:\nsimplicity sells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1257611,"text":"CA: Bravo. DP: Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1259302,"text":"CA: Hear, hear!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1260477,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}